/* Variance analysis on a YoY basis
If Budget > Actuals = Favorable
If Budget < Actuals = Unfavorable */

-- 2021 Variance Analysis
SELECT 
    EXTRACT(YEAR FROM transaction_date) AS "Year",
    department AS "Department",
    --category AS "Category",
    SUM(budget_amount) AS "Total Budget",
    SUM(actual_amount) AS "Total Actual",
    (SUM(budget_amount) - SUM(actual_amount)) AS "Variance",
    CASE 
        WHEN (SUM(budget_amount) - SUM(actual_amount)) >= 0 THEN 'Favorable'
        ELSE 'Unfavorable'
    END AS "Variance Status",
    SUM(actual_amount)/SUM(budget_amount) AS "Utilisation Rate"
FROM budget_vs_actual
WHERE EXTRACT(YEAR FROM transaction_date) = 2021
GROUP BY 
    EXTRACT(YEAR FROM transaction_date),
    department
    --category
/* to show only favorable expenses
HAVING 
    (SUM(budget_amount) - SUM(actual_amount)) >= 0
    */
ORDER BY 
    "Year",
    "Department",
    "Variance" ASC;

/* 2021 Findings
- All departments are in an overbudget capacity.
- Top 3 largest spenders and their utilisation rate are Finance (1.13), HR (1.08), and IT (1.07) which are support departments.
- Sales department is the lowest spender but still at overbudget.
- Top 5 Unfavorable Variances:
    Operations Department with Salaries
    Marketing Department with Marketing expense
    Marketing Deparmetn with Training expense
    Finance with Infrastructure
    Operations with Marketing expense
- The only favorable expenses are as follows:
    HR Department with Utilities expense at 21K
    IT Department with Infrastructure at 339K

Conclusions made based on findings:
    FY2021 is operating at an inefficiency. With all departments reporting an unfavorable variance, it signifies that the company has either overspent or failed to forecast external factors in changes price or quantity for the expenses.
*/

-- 2022 Variance Analysis
SELECT 
    EXTRACT(YEAR FROM transaction_date) AS "Year",
    department AS "Department",
    category AS "Category",
    SUM(budget_amount) AS "Total Budget",
    SUM(actual_amount) AS "Total Actual",
    (SUM(budget_amount) - SUM(actual_amount)) AS "Variance",
    CASE 
        WHEN (SUM(budget_amount) - SUM(actual_amount)) >= 0 THEN 'Favorable'
        ELSE 'Unfavorable'
    END AS "Variance Status",
    SUM(actual_amount)/SUM(budget_amount) AS "Utilisation Rate"
FROM budget_vs_actual
WHERE EXTRACT(YEAR FROM transaction_date) = 2022
GROUP BY 
    EXTRACT(YEAR FROM transaction_date),
    department,
    category
/* to show only favorable expenses
HAVING 
    (SUM(budget_amount) - SUM(actual_amount)) >= 0
    */
ORDER BY 
    "Year",
    "Department",
    "Variance" DESC;


